<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Archlinux on Less is more</title><link>https://andreyshuster.github.io/blog/archlinux/</link><description>Recent content in Archlinux on Less is more</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-US</language><copyright>Copyright Â© 2024, Andrey Shuster.</copyright><lastBuildDate>Fri, 14 Nov 2025 22:23:11 -0600</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://andreyshuster.github.io/blog/archlinux/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Update SteamOS packages</title><link>https://andreyshuster.github.io/update-steamos-packages/</link><pubDate>Fri, 14 Nov 2025 22:23:11 -0600</pubDate><guid>https://andreyshuster.github.io/update-steamos-packages/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;To update Arch Linux system packages you usually run:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo pacman-key --init
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo pacman-key --populate archlinux
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;However, for SteamOS is not enough. You will continue to get error about corrupted packages.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SteamOS packages are signed by their own GPG keys and they are need to populated too.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo pacman-key --populate holo
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;You&amp;rsquo;re welcome!&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>